# m6_p10_step_assist.shot — M6 P10 (2026-05-16)
#
# Verifies the general step-up assist in src/mech.c::apply_step_assist:
# paints a single 1-tile-tall solid obstacle on the slipstream floor,
# then walks a Trooper right into it. The mech should climb the step
# instead of wedging against it.
#
# Slipstream has a clean flat floor at row H-3 (row 47 for H=50, so the
# floor TOP is at y = 47 * 32 = 1504). We paint a 1-tile solid block at
# (tile_x=42, tile_y=46) which puts a 32-px-tall step at world x=1344,
# y=1472. The mech starts at world x=1280 just above the floor, then
# right-walks into the step.
#
# Verification (m6_p10_step_assist.log):
#   - The 'step_assist' SHOT_LOG line should fire at least once when the
#     leading foot reaches the step.
#   - By t=180, pelvis x should exceed 1400 (past the step base at 1344)
#     AND pelvis y should be ~960 px above the new step surface (i.e.
#     pelv.y < 1480 — pelvis standing on the raised tile, not wedged at
#     floor level y > 1500).
#
# A failing run shows the mech stuck at x ≈ 1340 with pelvis y near
# 1500 — wedged against the step.

window 1280 720
seed   42 7
out    build/shots/m6_p10_step_assist

map slipstream

# Paint a 1-tile-tall solid step on the floor at tile column 42.
# Floor top row is 47 (y=1504); the step tile is one row up, at row 46.
# 0x0001 = TILE_F_SOLID.
paint_tile 42 46 0x0001

loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

spawn_at 1280 1450
mouse    1280 600

at   1 press right

at  30 shot pre_step
at  90 shot at_step
at 180 shot post_step
at 220 end

contact_sheet step_sheet cols 3 cell 426 240
